cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.RO, cs.SY

This paper deals with the problem of routing in Flying Multi-hop Networks (FMNs) for providing Internet access using Unmanned Aerial Vehicles (UAVs). This topic falls under the category of Computer Networks and Communications (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a new routing metric that takes into account inter-flow interference, which is related to Information Theory (cs.IT) and Optimization and Control (cs.MA). The use of UAVs for network infrastructure also involves Robotics (cs.RO) and System and Control (cs.SY).
